java - hashmap - place each ele in hashmap, if it doesnt exist then put 1 or add one if it is already in hashmap, return the key whose value comes more than half of array length.




class Solution {
    public int majorityElement(int[] nums) {
        HashMap<Integer,Integer> map=new HashMap<>();

for (int n:nums){
	map.put(n,map.getOrDefault(n,0)+1);

	if (map.get(n)> nums.length/2){
		return n;
}
}
return -1;
    }




